message.content:
The DOS prompt is showing! The boot completed but 'win' command didn't execute properly. I can see "C:\>" at line 12. I need to add HIMEM.SYS back (needed for Windows) and send 'win' at the prompt.

{
  "analysis": "DOS boot completed. The prompt 'C:\\>' is visible. 'win' was echoed but didn't execute - likely because HIMEM.SYS is missing (needed for Windows 3.11 protected mode). Need to fix CONFIG.SYS to include HIMEM.SYS and then either restart or send 'win' manually.",
  "plan": "1. Update CONFIG.SYS with HIMEM.SYS back (but without SMARTDRV/IFSHLP). 2. Update AUTOEXEC.BAT with proper @ECHO OFF. 3. Restart QEMU. 4. Monitor until Windows starts.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /tmp/new_config2.sys << 'EOF'\nDEVICE=C:\\WINDOWS\\HIMEM.SYS\nDOS=HIGH\nFILES=30\nSHELL=C:\\DOS\\COMMAND.COM C:\\DOS\\ /p\nLASTDRIVE=Z\nSTACKS=9,256\nEOF\nmcopy -o -i /app/isos/win311.img@@32256 /tmp/new_config2.sys ::CONFIG.SYS\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /tmp/new_autoexec3.bat << 'BATEOF'\r\n@ECHO OFF\r\nPROMPT $p$g\r\nPATH C:\\WINDOWS;C:\\DOS\r\nSET TEMP=C:\\TEMP\r\nwin\r\nBATEOF\nmcopy -o -i /app/isos/win311.img@@32256 /tmp/new_autoexec3.bat ::AUTOEXEC.BAT\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mtype -i /app/isos/win311.img@@32256 ::CONFIG.SYS\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mtype -i /app/isos/win311.img@@32256 ::AUTOEXEC.BAT\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "kill $(pgrep qemu-system) 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; rm -f /tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup qemu-system-i386 -m 32 -hda /app/isos/win311.img -snapshot -vnc :1 -monitor unix:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock,server,nowait -vga cirrus -net nic,model=ne2k_isa -net user -boot c > /tmp/qemu.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sleep 15 && python3 /tmp/read_vga.py\n",
      "duration": 20.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
